Currently if you go browse->space admin you get prompted with websudo. However, only a handful of links under space admin actually requires it (remove space, permissions, restricted pages, mail accounts, mailbox import). All the other does not require webs sudo. This gives a very odd user experience, as you can go browse->advanced->edit space details (which is on the space admin screen). But you can not go browse->space admin_edit space details without entering your password.

A solution would be to have the Space Admin link take you to edit space details instead of the permissions page. It would also be nice to either add an icon, or otherwise visually indicate that some options will require you to websudo.

