This creates problems for clients of the REST service. That is, you'll query for a user using REST and it will return a JSON result with type "user". All your subsequent client code than has to translate this new constant to PersonalInformation.CONTENT_TYPE, as the bulk of Confluence code base uses it. 

This doesn't make sense to me given the class is also called the PersonalInformationContentEntityBuilder.

The CSS from the documentation theme is intefering with other styles from wiki page content.  The bug has already been discussed [here|http://forums.atlassian.com/message.jspa?messageID=257338634] but I've also just come across it when using the {table} macros.

Although the bus shows itself when using 3rd party macros, it's due to some very wide ranging CSS which over-rides a lot of over CSS and would appear to be acting beyond it's mandate.

The bug can be found in the splitter.css file 
{code}
body, p, td, table, tr, .bodytext, .stepfield, .wiki-content p, .panelContent{
    color: #333;
    background:none;
}
{code}

The bug can be found in the splitter.css file 

The *background:none* section seems to be wiping out other colour backgrounds as it takes priority.  Changing the code sample to this fixes the problem.

{code}
body, p, td, table, tr, .bodytext, .stepfield, .wiki-content p, .panelContent{
    color: #333;
}
{code}

